{"_id":"1Y6Fu7uAsItBBYsl","name":"Dog of War","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You are an active mercenary making money from conflicts, and you&rsquo;re recognizable for it. For the purposes of securing money, either when Earning during play or performing an Income Endeavour, refer to the following table:</p>\n<table style=\"width: 98.4694%; height: 80px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 33.0447%; height: 16px;\">Career Level</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 65.66%; height: 16px;\">Bonus Money per time the Talent is taken</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 33.0447%; height: 16px;\">1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 65.66%; height: 16px;\">+1d10 Silver Shillings</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 33.0447%; height: 16px;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 65.66%; height: 16px;\">+2d10 Silver Shillings</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 33.0447%; height: 16px;\">3</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 65.66%; height: 16px;\">+3d10 Silver Shillings</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 33.0447%; height: 16px;\">4</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 65.66%; height: 16px;\">\n<p>+1 Gold Crown</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Because of your profession, you are bound to make enemies. Opposition to the employers who hire you for your services consider you lower Status than them and might even harbor additional Psychologies such as Prejudice or Hatred as determined by the GM&mdash;perhaps you have cost them a chunk of land, destroyed their business, killed a loved one of theirs or see you simply as foreign scum. Because of this, opposing forces such as military and law enforcement run by your contractor&rsquo;s enemies are always suspicious of you and your company and suspect your motivations, which only gets worse the more times you have this Talent, with the exact implications determined by the GM.</p>\n<p>The scale of these oppositions might be something small such as villages or towns up to entire provinces or cities depending on the scale of the conflict. These penalties do not apply to mercenary work against widely opposed enemies of mankind, such as Beastmen, Greenskins, Dark Elves, Skaven or various monsters ravaging the countryside, among other known threats.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"max":{"type":"String","label":"Max Advances","value":"none"},"advances":{"type":"Number","label":"Advances","value":1},"career":{"value":"","type":"String","label":"Career"},"tests":{"type":"String","label":"Tests","value":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/wfrp4e-core/icons/talents/wealthy.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"AeiPIsFbYMHgAKXm","name":"Combat Might","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>Your strength of arms is so great you can wield weapons of massive size and weight with but one hand! You may wield any two-handed melee weapon with one hand with a -20 WS penalty. Any Melee Tests made wielding a two-handed weapon in one hand are replaced with Melee (Basic) as its primary Test. For each additional Talent level, the penalty is reduced by 10 until there is no penalty. At Talent level 3 you ignore any Slow or Tiring Weapon Flaws when wielding a melee weapon with both hands.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"max":{"type":"String","label":"Max Advances","value":"2"},"advances":{"type":"Number","label":"Advances","value":1},"career":{"value":"","type":"String","label":"Career"},"tests":{"type":"String","label":"Tests","value":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/wfrp4e-core/icons/talents/ambidextrous.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Vx2IN7tFgRYOjv5v","name":"Martial Artist","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You are a master of unarmed combat, capable of felling foes with your fists alone. Your Unarmed attacks no longer have the <em>Undamaging </em>Flaw. You may also Oppose incoming missile shots in your Line of Sight bare-handed. Roll an <strong>Opposed Melee (Brawling)</strong> against missiles being used against you, grabbing them harmlessly in mid-air if successful. Ranged weapons with the <em>Blackpowder </em>Quality ignore this Talent.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"max":{"type":"String","label":"Max Advances","value":"ws"},"advances":{"type":"Number","label":"Advances","value":1},"career":{"value":"","type":"String","label":"Career"},"tests":{"type":"String","label":"Tests","value":"Melee (Brawling)"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/wfrp4e-core/icons/talents/fast-hands.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"bgJAtvDV67bnUe6G","name":"Surgical Precision","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You have mastered the art of bringing down foes non-lethally. Whenever you deal a Critical Hit to an opponent, you may instead make an <strong>Average (+20) Intelligence</strong> Test. If you succeed, you inflict +1 <em>Fatigued </em>Condition upon your target for each SL you scored on the Intelligence Test. Further, you gain a +40 bonus to any Heal Test to treat the wounds of your target once they&rsquo;ve been subdued, assuming they&rsquo;re still alive.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"max":{"type":"String","label":"Max Advances","value":"s"},"advances":{"type":"Number","label":"Advances","value":1},"career":{"value":"","type":"String","label":"Career"},"tests":{"type":"String","label":"Tests","value":"Melee tests when trying to bring down a foe non-lethally"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/wfrp4e-core/icons/talents/dirty-fighting.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"gO9QSxBmZkpLNNcv","name":"Lightning Strike","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>Your blade is as swift as lightning! You strike before your opponent even has time to react. As an Action, you may spend all your Advantage to attempt a single Unopposed Melee Test against your target, so long as your opponent is using a weapon without the Fast Quality. This action requires a Fast Quality weapon and sacrifices your Free Action and remaining Movement, if any, for the remainder of the turn if used.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"max":{"type":"String","label":"Max Advances","value":"ag"},"advances":{"type":"Number","label":"Advances","value":1},"career":{"value":"","type":"String","label":"Career"},"tests":{"type":"String","label":"Tests","value":"Melee Test when using Lightning Strike talent"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/wfrp4e-core/icons/talents/riposte.png","effects":[]}